# Layout Template

## Summary
LayoutTemplate is a reusable floor arrangement: a `name` plus `tables = containsMany(Table)` and `fixtures = containsMany(Fixture)` capturing the positioned tables and fixtures (dance floor, stage, bar, and so on) of a room setup, with computed `tableCount` and `seatCount` totals. In the Table Seating Planner, the template browser finds LayoutTemplate instances by card type and applies one to stamp its tables and fixtures onto the current plan; you can also save the plan's current arrangement back as a new template. The shipped examples cover a ceremony and a reception layout.

## Import
```js
import { LayoutTemplate } from '../layout-template';
```

## Usage
LayoutTemplate is a card, so consuming cards link to it:

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksTo } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { LayoutTemplate } from '../layout-template';

export class VenueSetup extends CardDef {
  @field layout = linksTo(LayoutTemplate);
}
```

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.layout @format='embedded' />
```
Renders the template as a thumbnail preview of its floor plan with table and seat counts.
